</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6FC01E647DBA8D0927FCFC57821DC93" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B9BEF6686E359040858E5C933F974006" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A586B52A81851D49DF7F5DE10B8ACC8" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">This species is named in honor of Mr. Xiao-Yu Zhu who collected some specimens of the new species.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5E966E8767F6562F7EE0B5927BAB05A6" pageId="3" pageNumber="52" type="notes">
<paragraph id="3D27C22BC98F8923444F80E068FB60E3" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">Biological notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="36AA8648C58632A4CC089FC25F969299" pageId="3" pageNumber="52">This species was found gathering on an unknown fungus on a huge rotten log across stream, and was observed to become active when night fell (Figs 11, 12).</paragraph>
